  ----------------------------------------------------------
  The goals of Online Transaction Processing (OLTP) and data analytics are fundamentally different. OLTP is designed to handle high-volume, real-time transactions, ensuring that customers can complete their purchases quickly and efficiently. It focuses on speed and reliability, prioritizing the processing of transactions as quickly as possible to minimize wait times and maintain a positive customer experience.
  
  On the other hand, data analytics aims to extract insights and patterns from large datasets to provide actionable information. This involves analyzing historical data to identify trends, predict future outcomes, and make informed decisions. Data analytics is often used to support strategic planning, marketing, and product development, among other areas.
  
  In summary, OLTP is focused on real-time transaction processing, while data analytics is concerned with extracting insights from large datasets. Both are critical components of modern business operations, but they serve different purposes and require different approaches to implementation and management.
